A photo from a competition.

99
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:36,880
Aiping.

100
00:05:38,630 --> 00:05:39,470
Xiao Han.

101
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:42,560
We will

102
00:05:43,430 --> 00:05:44,950
never forget Youguang.

103
00:05:46,160 --> 00:05:47,950
No matter how times change,

104
00:05:48,360 --> 00:05:50,170
in the hearts of the people
from No. 9 Factory,

105
00:05:50,480 --> 00:05:51,320
he…

106
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:53,430
will always have a place.

107
00:06:05,750 --> 00:06:06,800
Thank you, Director Dong.

108
00:06:12,270 --> 00:06:13,110
Thank you.

109
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:15,390
Thank you all.

110
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:25,160
Brother Xiao Han!

111
00:06:26,740 --> 00:06:27,830
There you are.

112
00:06:29,190 --> 00:06:30,870
We are preparing
for the group photo.

113
00:06:31,630 --> 00:06:32,470
Okay.

114
00:06:32,510 --> 00:06:33,390
I know.

115
00:06:34,950 --> 00:06:36,240
What are you looking at?

116
00:06:39,750 --> 00:06:41,950
"I leave no trace of wings in the air,

117
00:06:42,840 --> 00:06:44,630
(Tagore)
but I am glad I have had my flight."

118
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:46,040
A quote my dad copied.

119
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:47,950
It's the first time I've seen it.

120
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:50,160
It's from Tagore's poetry.

121
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:53,750
"I leave no trace of wings in the air,

122
00:06:54,750 --> 00:06:56,830
but I am glad I have had my flight."

123
00:06:58,950 --> 00:07:00,150
What does it express?

124
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:01,440
It's about my dad.

125
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:05,040
And No. 9 Factory.

126
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:09,680
Even though they are no longer with us,

127
00:07:10,750 --> 00:07:11,630
they were here once,

128
00:07:12,340 --> 00:07:13,820
and will always be remembered.

129
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:21,430
Let's go back to take the photo.

130
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:23,240
Actually,

131
00:07:23,380 --> 00:07:25,240
I plan to write a story
about No. 9 Factory.

132
00:07:25,510 --> 00:07:26,410
Our story.

133
00:07:26,630 --> 00:07:27,470
Really?

134
00:07:27,870 --> 00:07:28,870
Tell me more.

135
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:30,600
I want to submit it
to the school journal.

136
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:32,480
If the editor likes it

137
00:07:32,490 --> 00:07:33,360
and it's published,

138
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:34,360
you'll see it.

139
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:35,750
If not,

140
00:07:35,750 --> 00:07:37,310
I won't embarrass myself.

141
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:39,620
Then I'll wait to see it in the journal.

142
00:07:45,090 --> 00:07:46,070
Are you ready over there?

143
00:07:46,070 --> 00:07:48,030
(Shanghai Puyang No. 9 Cotton Textile Factory
Memorial Museum)

144
00:07:48,030 --> 00:07:49,430
Time to take photos!

145
00:07:49,430 --> 00:07:50,310
Quick now.

146
00:07:50,310 --> 00:07:52,920
History only records
the stories of heroes,

147
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:56,190
- You can stand on the stools.
- and those legendary figures.

148
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:58,950
Those forgotten,

149
00:07:59,430 --> 00:08:00,560
eliminated,

150
00:08:01,070 --> 00:08:02,190
or submerged

151
00:08:02,390 --> 00:08:05,030
(Memo: A Group of Interesting People)
seem like they never existed.

152
00:08:06,190 --> 00:08:08,680
I used to admire heroes,

153
00:08:09,190 --> 00:08:11,560
but now I've changed.

154
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:14,490
More than the great figures
in the history books,

155
00:08:15,270 --> 00:08:16,870
what resonates with me the most

156
00:08:17,430 --> 00:08:20,390
are those unnoticed ordinary people.

157
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:23,460
- What truly touches people
- Come up to the front.

158
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:25,480
are their lived experiences, their tears,

159
00:08:26,270 --> 00:08:28,000
and their everyday life.

160
00:08:28,830 --> 00:08:30,190
I want to write a song of praise

161
00:08:30,830 --> 00:08:33,200
for ordinary people, making them heroes.

162
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,600
Three, two, one.

163
00:08:35,270 --> 00:08:36,120
Cheese!

